response.Q0: I would just click on the outer nodes and choose the one with the highest payoff or lowest penalty to be the path for the spider. Each round I would try to click on outer nodes I hadn't done before.
response.Q1: I focused on the outer nodes' values more than the path to get to them. I found it best to only reveal three nodes and then make a choice to minimize the penalties from revealing nodes.
response.Q2: It was not very difficult, it was more about making a decision as quickly as possible with the greatest rewards out of the known options.
